  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ACCOUNTS OFFICER",
  "description": "<p>Zagro is a Singapore private-limited company, strong in heritage and very experienced in providing Agrisolutions to farmers in agriculture and animal husbandry. It manufactures and distributes a wide range of nutrition and protection products for animal health and crop care.</p><p>In line with our aggressive growth, we are now looking for an energetic, driven and highly competent professional who is passionate and committed to join our growing talent pool and make a difference to the success and future of our Group.</p><p><strong>ACCOUNTS OFFICER</strong></p><p><em>Job Responsibilities: -</em></p><p>•\tHandle and process payments efficiently and accurately</p><p>•\tPrepare monthly bank reconciliations</p><p>•\tAssist in month-end closing activities and management reporting.</p><p>•\tManage company’s full set of accounts independently.</p><p>•\tYear-end reconciliation, prepare schedules and quarterly GST returns.</p><p>•\tPerform any other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the immediate superior.<br /></p><p><em>Requirements: -</em></p><p>•\tDegree, Diploma, LCCI, CAT, or equivalent qualification</p><p>•\tAt least 3 years of relevant working experience.</p><p>•\tProficiency in ACCPAC Accounting Software will be an added advantage.</p><p>•\tMeticulous, responsible, and able to work independently with minimal supervision.</p>",
